The bodies of an elderly couple have been found in a house in Tipperary. Both deceased were aged in their 70s and their bodies are believed to have been in the house for a considerable period of time before their discovery. Investigations are at an early stage but preliminary examinations suggest there is no sign of foul play.. The bodies of the man and woman were discovered in the home in Cloneen, Co. Tipperary, near Clonmel, just after 4pm after neighbours alerted gardaí the couple had not been seen for some time. A Garda investigation has been launched and the scene has been preserved pending an examination by the Garda Technical Bureau. The State Pathologist’s Office has been notified and autopsies are expected to be carried out on the remains to establish the cause of death